As you might have heard once or a thousand times, it=E2=80=99s been a humbl=
ing year or so in the art market. Naturally, that economic climate has had =
downstream consequences for the adjacent businesses that support the market=
 and its actors, including Artnet, the German auction database, news site, =
and sales brokerage business. Within the art industry, the brand remains ve=
ry powerful, possibly as esteemed among insiders as Sotheby=E2=80=99s and C=
hristie=E2=80=99s are with the general public. But according to a newly rel=
eased financial report ( https://www.artnet.com/investor-relations/annual-r=
eports/240831_artnet_AnnualReport_EN.pdf?utm_campaign=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCR=
IBERS+%289%2F17%2F24%29&utm_content=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%289%2F1%2F2=
4%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617=
da42abd12a ),
the company has struggled, losing about $1 million in 2023=E2=80=94a revers=
al from a small net profit the year before=E2=80=94due in part to declining=
 revenue in its auction and private sales business. Also buried within the =
report, Artnet revealed it took loans totaling approximately $2 million fro=
m a third party, a senior executive, and the former C.E.O., presumably to c=
over operating losses.

On one level, Artnet held its own amid a downturn, only losing 4 percent of=
 the previous year=E2=80=99s topline revenue. =E2=80=9C2023 was a difficult=
 year for us and the entire art market,=E2=80=9D C.E.O. Jacob Pabst wrote i=
n a letter accompanying the financial report. =E2=80=9CAs a result, sales a=
t the major auction houses plummeted, as did our own.=E2=80=9D Pabst also p=
reviewed a significant restructuring program. =E2=80=9CThe cost reduction m=
easures have already become evident in 2023, with savings of over 1.5 milli=
on USD,=E2=80=9D he wrote, =E2=80=9Cto which an additional 3.5 million USD =
will be added this year.
In 2025, these measures will then fully take effect, resulting in savings o=
f nearly 6 million USD.=E2=80=9D For a company that does around $25 million=
 in revenue, cost savings of that magnitude would be a real achievement.

Alas, this financial engineering may be necessary to stave off a leadership=
 change at the publicly traded firm. The value of Artnet=E2=80=99s brand, a=
s I tried to explain ( https://puck.news/could-artnet-founder-be-forced-out=
/?utm_campaign=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%289%2F17%2F24%29&utm_content=3DW=
all+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%289%2F1%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_sour=
ce=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) earlier this year, has att=
racted R=C3=BCdiger Weng, who is looking to oust Pabst=E2=80=99s father, Ha=
ns Neuendorf, the company=E2=80=99s founder and former C.E.O., and the rest=
 of the Neuendorf family from control. Per the report, at the end of last y=
ear, Weng owned 28.83 percent of Artnet=E2=80=99s stock through his firm, W=
eng Fine Art, which eclipsed the
26.65 percent position held by Galerie Neuendorf, the Berlin-based entity c=
ontrolled by Hans. The two sides are competing for the votes of a handful o=
f other large investors, with the issue expected to come to a head at the a=
nnual general meeting, a shareholder gathering originally slated for August=
 but that remains unscheduled.

The last time I wrote about Artnet, the company was unhappy with my piece. =
One of Artnet=E2=80=99s complaints was that I had misstated Neuendorf=E2=80=
=99s compensation. I had written that Neuendorf=E2=80=99s consultancy agree=
ment with Artnet included a fee of $325,000. (The correct number, revealed =
in the annual report, is =E2=82=AC336,000 for 2022. That fee was reduced to=
 =E2=82=AC161,000 in 2023.) For this article, I sent emails to Pabst and hi=
s brother, Albert Neuendorf, Artnet=E2=80=99s chief strategy officer, askin=
g to discuss the company=E2=80=99s financial statements. I received no repl=
y. I wrote to them again this morning, and included their sister Sophie
Neuendorf as well. They did not respond to my requests for comment.

