MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6MTAzNzUyOX0/6aea19836e1577cef67eef91d93fc4e=
3ea8bb132ca0207f18609784913bf14eb" style=3D"color:#d40000;text-decoration:n=
one;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">here</a></u>.) What also stands out in =
the annual report=E2=80=94besides the growing losses on what appears to be =
a stable business=E2=80=94is the fact that beyond Hans Neuendorf=E2=80=99s =
consulting arrangement with Artnet, there are other related-party arrangeme=
nts, such as a =E2=82=AC66,000 payment to a member of the management board =
for design work, and a =E2=82=AC118,000 consultation payment to another mem=
ber of the board. There are also loans in the amounts of =E2=82=AC492,000 f=
rom an Artnet executive and =E2=82=AC511,000 from Galerie Neuendorf, as wel=
l as that additional $1 million loan from a private party in New York. <br/=
><br/>If you were a shareholder in Artnet, you might be wondering why a
moderately healthy company, which admittedly has some low-margin businesses=
, keeps falling behind. That=E2=80=99s the background to the upcoming annua=
l general meeting. If and when it gets scheduled, I=E2=80=99ll be curious t=
o learn more=E2=80=94as I=E2=80=99m sure you will be, as well. <br/></td>
